equation} \par Because $x$ is large, we perform the change of variables $u = \sqrt{x \frac{|f''(0.455137201554065)|}{2}}(t-0.455137201554065)$, rewriting the integral as \begin{equation} g(0.455137201554065) e^{- x f(0.455137201554065)} \int_{\sqrt{x \frac{|f''(0.455137201554065)|}{2}} (a-0.455137201554065)}^{\sqrt{x \frac{|f''(0.455137201554065)|}{2}} (b-0.455137201554065)} \sqrt{\frac{2}{x |f''(0.455137201554065)|}} e^{-u^2} \, dt \end{equation} \par Since $x \to \infty$, we approximate this as \begin{equation} g(0.455137201554065) e^{- x f(0.455137201554065)} \sqrt{\frac{2}{x |f''(0.455137201554065)|} } \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} e^{-u^2} \, dt \end{equation} \par Solving the integral and evaluating, we find that \par \begin{equation} \boxed{I(x) \approx 0.719832722044118 \sqrt{\pi} \sqrt{\frac{1}{x}} e^{0.157699686244314 x}} \end{equation}

